 KAIZER Chiefs string of announcements of players who will not be part of the club next season continued on Thursday as they announced the termination of Dumisani Zuma's contract.The 27-year-old midfielder had one year remaining in his contract, which was set to lapse at the end of next season. However, Amakhosi have decided to let him go citing "numerous disciplinary issues"."Attacking midfielder Dumsani Zuma's numerous disciplinary issues have led to the Club letting him go with a year still remaining on his contract," the club said in a brief statement."This follows his latest appearance in front of the DC, which resulted in his dismissal as recommended by an independent authority. The 27-year-old only featured three times in 2021/22 for Chiefs."Since joining from Bloemfontein Celtic in 2017, he has been suspended a number of times, including twice in one season. He was also sent to rehab and counselling in the season that just ended. Over five seasons, he played 100 matches (25 starts + 75 subs) and scored 13 goals.""We wish Dumi well in the future."Late last year, Zuma was suspended by the club after he was reportedly found guilty of driving under the influence of alcohol while he was injured at the time.After being fully fit and having also gone through the rehabilitation process, the 26-year-old recently returned to the match-day squad and made his first cameo of the season during Chiefs' 1-0 loss to Stellenbosch last month. On his return from a 10-month absence, which included being suspended and undergoing rehabilitation processes, Zuma was suspended again after Chiefs lost 2-1 to Cape Town City. Player Updates: Attacking midfielder Dumsani Zuma’s numerous disciplinary issues have led to the Club letting him go with a year still remaining on his contract... #Amakhosi4Life pic.twitter.com/hXRhPEKkVR  